                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/2820.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-02-18T12:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 18, 1912—12 noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Serious conditions in Sinaloa, with many complaints from Americans and no
                    protection outlying cities. Messengers arriving at Saltillo report 3,000 mounted
                    rebels before Torreon. Armed revolution exists States of Pueblo and Tlaxcala,
                    and some towns have been taken. Condition in Morelos and Guerrero the same.</p>
                <p>Government will probably ask Congress to suspend constitutional guaranties
                    throughout the Republic.</p>
                <p>Vásquez Gómez, by proclamation from San Antonio, assumed provisional presidency
                    to-day.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
